{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"DOMQuad","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMQuad","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Geometry_interfaces\">Geometry interfaces</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMQuad\"><code>DOMQuad</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Geometry Interfaces</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrix\"><code>DOMMatrix</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMMatrixReadOnly\"><code>DOMMatrixReadOnly</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMPoint\"><code>DOMPoint</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRect\"><code>DOMRect</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRectReadOnly\"><code>DOMRectReadOnly</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>A <code>DOMQuad</code> is a collection of four <code>DOMPoint</code>s defining the corners of an arbitrary quadrilateral. Returning <code>DOMQuad</code>s lets <code>getBoxQuads()</code> return accurate information even when arbitrary 2D or 3D transforms are present. It has a handy <code>bounds</code> attribute returning a <code>DOMRectReadOnly</code> for those cases where you just want an axis-aligned bounding rectangle.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"constructor","title":"Constructor","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"domquad\"><a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>DOMQuad()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Creates a new <code>DOMQuad</code> object.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"properties","title":"Properties","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"p1p2p3p4\">p1,p2,p3,p4 <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>are <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMPoint\"><code>DOMPoint</code></a> objects for each of the <code>DOMQuad</code> object's four corners.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"domquad.fromrect\"><a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>DOMQuad.fromRect()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a new <code>DOMQuad</code> object based on the passed set of coordinates.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"domquad.fromquad\"><a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>DOMQuad.fromQuad()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a new <code>DOMQuad</code> object based on the passed set of coordinates.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"domquad.getbounds\"><a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>DOMQuad.getBounds()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMRect\"><code>DOMRect</code></a> object with the coordinates and dimensions of the <code>DOMQuad</code> object.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"domquad.tojson\"><a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>DOMQuad.toJSON()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a JSON representation of the <code>DOMQuad</code> object.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://drafts.fxtf.org/geometry/#DOMQuad","title":"Geometry Interfaces Module Level 1"}],"query":"api.DOMQuad"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.DOMQuad","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMQuad/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Constructor","id":"constructor"},{"text":"Properties","id":"properties"},{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"A DOMQuad is a collection of four DOMPoints defining the corners of an arbitrary quadrilateral. Returning DOMQuads lets getBoxQuads() return accurate information even when arbitrary 2D or 3D transforms are present. It has a handy bounds attribute returning a DOMRectReadOnly for those cases where you just want an axis-aligned bounding rectangle.","popularity":0.0002,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:10:34.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"DOMQuad","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"DOMQuad","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/domquad","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/domquad/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/1511e914c6b1ce6f88056bfefd48a6aa585cebce","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMQuad","title":"DOMQuad"}],"pageTitle":"DOMQuad - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}